  "texts": [
    "For example, a low or zero value for the face condition means that the underlying mechanism of the ERP is not related to face processing.",
    "A high SHERPA value for an ERP component indicates that the component has a strong positive contribution to the predictive outcome of the model, meaning that it is a critical component for predicting the outcome variable (again, face processing).",
    "Most importantly, the output scale is linear.",
    "For example, when comparing two SHERPA peaks and one is twice as high as the other, that means it is twice as important.",
